07/04/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Domestic violence claimed 16 lives in 2009, according to Albania's national council for gender equality. Speaking on Tuesday (April 6th), Labour Minister Spiro Ksera said that 1,217 domestic violence cases were reported overall, a significant increase compared to 2008. The National Institute of Statistics has a project under way to identify all victims and reported cases, as a prelude to action by lawmakers to combat the problem. (News 24, Top News, Telegrafi, NOA - 06/04/10)
